v2.0:
General:
continue to support console tools

  - cleanup as much as possible (emacs, old files)
  - install: backup the first copy of a configfile, the backup will be next to the config file
  - automatic aldebaran mode if running on a box inside aldebaran
  - separate user configuration to file <configfile.rc>.custom next to <configfile.rc>
  - osx: be smart with cmake, etc..
  - config option to switch from emacs to vim as default editor (and others?)

setup:
  - use python for the installation
  - ask if user want to switch default shell to zsh
  - do not assume ctafconf's sources are in .config/ctafconf
  - store personal information to .config/ctafconf (install link from everywhere), remove the perso folder
  - simplify setup

GUI:
  - install
  - component installation
  - update
  - use the same lib as setup
  - change env variable
  - add/mod/suppr alias
  - handle profile

zsh:
  - allow for automatic sourcing of a config file when entering a directory
    and finding a .zenv or .env
    this config file should set a variable that would be displayed in the prompt
    to remember the special behaviors of the shell

